## Issue Drafted: Test Debt Workaround Culture üö®

I've drafted a **Bottstand Learning** issue in APGI-cmy/PartPulse based on your PR #211 review request:

````yaml type="draft-issue"
type: draft-issue
tag: "bottstand-test-debt-followup"
issueNumber: 0
repository: "APGI-cmy/PartPulse"
state: "draft"
title: "[BUG] Continuous workaround culture has led to significant test debt (Bottstand QA Follow-up)"
template: "defect-bug.yml"
labels: ["test debt", "bottstand learning"]
template-form-values:
    actual: Active presence of workaround comments, skipped tests, test stubs, or partial passes being tolerated. Agents and/or maintainers repeatedly defer fixes, treating problems as non-blockers. Accumulated test debt has arisen.
    checklist: true,true,true,true
    description: "Continuous workaround culture using comments (e.g., TODOs or 'will fix later') is pre-existing in this codebase. These have accumulated into significant test debt over time, leading to a pattern where known broken or incomplete tests are tolerated as non-blockers. This practice masks underlying problems, delays remediation, and creates bottlenecks for future delivery. \n\nThis issue is to be recorded as a Bottstand Learning and should be referenced as part of the QA escalation trail. Agent/maintainers must not use workaround comments as substitutes for proper test completion. All test debt must be immediately remediated as per STOP-AND-FIX and Zero Test Debt constitutional doctrine.\n\nThe agent is instructed to immediately:\n- Run all relevant QA and governance-driven tests (including lint, coverage, typecheck, test-dodging checks)\n- Identify all test debt instances (skipped tests, TODOs, .only, commented-out, stubs, unfinished test infra)\n- Fully resolve all test debt, re-running all gates and validations\n- Attach a PREHANDOVER_PROOF with evidence of zero test debt before any further handover\n\nThis issue is also to be escalated to the canonical governance repo as a Bottstand QA learning.\n"
    discoverer: copilot (auto-generated based on PR followup request)
    environment: |
        - Environment: All (production/staging/local)
        - Version: Current HEAD
        - Date/Time: 2026-01-26
    evidence: 'Workaround comments in source, skipped tests, TODOs, coverage suppressions. Also previous PREHANDOVER_PROOFs referencing incomplete test removals or skipped validation as blockers. See PR #211 history.'
    expected: No workaround or 'should pass eventually' comments anywhere in the test suite. 100% of tests must be either complete or escalated to governance as blocking/irreducible debt (which is not acceptable per current doctrine).
    impact: |
        - Affected users: All users, agents, and maintainers relying on truthful test status
        - Affected functionality: All test coverage and build-critical paths are implicated
        - Business impact: Future regressions, hidden failures, and maintainability threats
    notes: This issue should be recorded as a Bottstand Learning, and governance escalation is already planned. Agents must review the governance-liaison agent contract to ensure STOP-AND-FIX and Zero Test Debt lock sections are present and enforced (they currently are, per review).
    reproduction: |
        1. Locate files marked with TODOs, FIXME, or similar 'workaround' comments
        2. Run `npm test` and `npm run lint` to surface all errors/warnings
        3. Inspect test suites for .skip(), .only, commented-out or empty test definitions
        4. List all legitimate test gaps and stubs
        5. Remediate all test debt and repeat QA validation
        6. Attach PREHANDOVER_PROOF showing debt-free status
    severity: HIGH - Major functionality broken, significant user impact
    workaround: 'Intermittent: workaround comments may reduce test urgency, but do not provide real mitigation.'
template-form-labels:
    actual: Actual Behavior
    checklist: Reporter Checklist
    description: Defect Description
    discoverer: Discovered By
    environment: Environment
    evidence: Evidence
    expected: Expected Behavior
    impact: Impact Assessment
    notes: Additional Notes
    reproduction: Reproduction Steps
    severity: Severity
    workaround: Workaround
````

