repository: "APGI-cmy/maturion-foreman-office-app"
state: "draft"
title: "[FOLLOW-UP] Systemic YAML validation test debt: Ecosystem-wide STOP-AND-FIX remediation ‚Äì see PR #679"
description: |-
    ### Context
    In PR #679 ([Batch 9: Layer down activation, domain & execution governance](https://github.com/APGI-cmy/maturion-foreman-office-app/pull/679)), a systemic issue was observed and resolved: multiple agent files contained accumulated YAML formatting and validation errors, which had been masked by incorrect validation workflows (validating whole .md files instead of extracting YAML front matter). This was discovered during STOP-AND-FIX enforcement and immediately remediated in the same PR.

    ### Problem
    The underlying pattern matches the earlier test debt bottleneck observed in PartPulse (issue #212):
    - The ecosystem previously tolerated pre-existing YAML formatting and validation workarounds.
    - Immediate STOP-AND-FIX response in PR #679 led to >6,800 lines of YAML/metadata corrections in 7 agents files (massive validation debt).
    - No "will fix later" comments were left and all debt was remediated pre-handover, but this highlights the **importance of rigorously enforcing STOP-AND-FIX and test debt doctrine for agent contract validation**.

    ### Bottstand Learning / Governance
    - The governance-liaison agent contract now locks down Zero Warning handover and STOP-AND-FIX as MANDATORY.
    - However, this systemic validation methodology drift (whole file vs frontmatter) affected the entire ecosystem before full enforcement.
    - **Actionable Learning:** All future validation workflow modifications must be benchmarked against real file usage *and* cross-repo evidence, not just superficial tool documentation.
    - **Escalation:** This follow-up should be referenced in the canonical governance repo as a Bottstand Learning (see also PartPulse #212), and triggers a revalidation/benchmark audit across all consumer and governance repos' agent validation logic.

    ### Requested Actions
    1. Document this as a permanent Bottstand QA follow-up to Batch 9 and link to the PR.
    2. Require governance maintainers to periodically audit actual vs declared validation workflow behavior on agent files.
    3. Reaffirm that ZERO TEST DEBT AND STOP-AND-FIX are locked as immutable for ALL agent contract validation.

    ---
    Related PR: #679
    Related issue: [PartPulse #212](https://github.com/APGI-cmy/PartPulse/issues/212)
assignees: ["APGI-cmy"]
labels: ["governance-violation"]
blockedByTags: ["APGI-cmy/maturion-foreman-office-app#679"]
````

