s include, but are not limited to: "nitpicking", "can fix next time", "not in my assignment/domain", "YAML/script only", "non-blocking", "stylistic", "old code", etc.\n>  - 100% means full, objective, zero-excuse resolution. "If I see it, I own it. If I can't fix it, I must escalate without delay."\n>  - Excuses do not demote a failure from "blocking" to "non-blocking". All failures are blocking until fixed or escalated with governance justification.\n>  - Agents *must* proactively report and escalate issues in protected files, other domains, or code they cannot modify‚Äîsilence is governance violation.\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n- Approve governance update to STOP-AND-FIX, Test Debt, Test Dodging, and PR Gate canons.\n- Integrate specific forbidden-excuse lists and escalation mechanisms across all agent contracts\n- Escalate learning to Bootstrap Learnings.\n- Develop continuous regression audit on excuse-based deferral in reviews.\n\n\n**Assignee:** APGI-cmy, governance-repo-administrator\n**Labels:** governance, enhancement, STOP-AND-FIX, test-debt, test-dodging, learning, anti-pattern\n\n---\n*Copilot is powered by AI, so mistakes are possible. Leave feedback via the üëç üëé to help improve the experience.*"
